Thon Tarliser 56 Magician - aka CoH Slut - Brothers of Darkness&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
I paid all in total 320 - 350k plat for the 3 MQs I needed.<br>
<br>
Since I was out of work for about 7 months farming for plat was not so hard.  Employed back in a decent position now EQ is now more or less a very distant priority.<br>
<br>
Under normal situations I would have simply given up on the epic since farming for plat is time consuming and boring.<br>
<br>
The guilds on Saryrn that are large enough to help a mage obtain the Air crown or farm Hate every week for months are most certainly chaotic nutral if not evil.<br>
<br>
Start a level 1 character on Sayrn and go see for yourself, you could claim you were an &quot;uber mage&quot; on &lt;insert server&gt;, and see how far that will get you as you level up.<br>
<br>
You could ofcouse try to make friends and get into a great guild and then find out that the big guilds treat their mages like waste products.  By the time I started a character on Saryrn all the guilds that could help me do my epic had enough Magicians for CoH and by the time I was 60 they had thier Mala slaves as well.<br>
<br>
When one finally was interested when I was level 60 I decided not to bother since they expected me to pay 15k+ plat to buy new resist gear and then be happy giving them my password so they could play me for coh and mala if I was busy and could not be on.<br>
<br>
Sorry.. that goes against SoE/VI policy on player account secruity.<br>
<br>
Not all servers are full of nice folks willing to give people a chance and work with classes that are deemed broken.<br>
<br>
Just because you lucked out and picked the right server to be on does not mean there are many of us here that both like the class but dislike the fact we as Magicians are so poorly desired and so rarely helped.<br>
<br>
I tried to put my time in helping others but the people I helped so soon forgot that I did when it was time for me to complete my epic.<br>
<br>
I have a close small group of friends I help now and thats it.  I am not interested in helping anyone beyond that because greed and dislike of any class that does not seem to offer immediate solid group benifit has turned EQ into &quot;not a nice place&quot; to quote the Saryrn Tavern message board theme.<br>
<br>
